  <title>13.5.2 Processing When NC Is Reset</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading4">Processing When NC Is Reset</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">In the event the NC is reset while the user I/O interface function M code is being executed, the M code is reset and program is terminated, but the operation continues. M codes, which not executed yet when NC reset is pressed, will not be executed.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">If NC reset is pressed when no user I/O interface functions M codes are being executed, the output status of all output signals remains the same.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
